        This method should be called right after the creation of this class's instance, before any property in other config modules is used. Check each config modules are created properly and override their properties if necessary.

      • shouldJvmRefer

        protected boolean shouldJvmRefer(Map<String,String> map)
        Figure out should refer the service in the same JVM from configurations. The default behavior is true 1. if injvm is specified, then use it 2. then if a url is specified, then assume it's a remote call 3. otherwise, check scope parameter 4. if scope is not specified but the target service is provided in the same JVM, then prefer to make the local call, which is the default behavior
